Subject: [PATCH] firmware: imx: select SOC_BUS to fix firmware build
Git-commit: 82c082784e03a9a9c043345f9bc04bc8254cf6da
Patch-mainline: v5.11-rc6
References: git-fixes

Fix build error in firmware/imx/ selecting SOC_BUS.

Riscv32-linux-ld: drivers/firmware/imx/imx-scu-soc.o: in function `.L9':
imx-scu-soc.c:(.text+0x1b0): undefined reference to `soc_device_register'

Fixes: edbee095fafb ("firmware: imx: add SCU firmware driver support")
Signed-off-by: Randy Dunlap <rdunlap@infradead.org>
Reported-by: kernel test robot <lkp@intel.com>
Cc: Atish Patra <atish.patra@wdc.com>
Cc: Palmer Dabbelt <palmerdabbelt@google.com>
Cc: Ard Biesheuvel <ardb@kernel.org>
Cc: Anson Huang <Anson.Huang@nxp.com>
Cc: Daniel Baluta <daniel.baluta@nxp.com>
Reviewed-by: Dong Aisheng <aisheng.dong@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: Shawn Guo <shawnguo@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/firmware/imx/Kconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/firmware/imx/Kconfig b/drivers/firmware/imx/Kconfig
index 1d2e5b85d7ca..c027d99f2a59 100644
--- a/drivers/firmware/imx/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/firmware/imx/Kconfig
@@ -13,6 +13,7 @@ config IMX_DSP
 config IMX_SCU
 	bool "IMX SCU Protocol driver"
 	depends on IMX_MBOX
+	select SOC_BUS
 	help
